<p><font face="Arial" color="#004A95"><strong><big><big>A ‘Perfect’ New Millennium @ The Hanover Grand</big></big></strong></font></p>

<table border="0" width="750">
  <tr>
    <td width="115" valign="top" bgcolor="#002D42"><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">club
    beat news</font></td>
    <td width="417" bgcolor="#002D42"><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">Report written by
      for clubber.co.uk</font><p><font face="Arial" color="#FFFFFF">TONI TAMBOURINE and his party crew are lining up a marathon millennium that will rock the capital. The man with the plan will be counting down the close of the year with a no expense spared ‘FUTURE PERFECT’ celebration. The king of the carousal will lead his troops into 2000 with a bang, giving the Millennium Dome a run for its money! <p> This 48 hour extravaganza comes as an all inclusive package for just £99 for two unsurpassable nights at Mayfair’s most illustrious venue. WARNING! - This is not a soiree for the faint hearted! Toni, Twysden and their glamorous troops are already in training for a 48 hour centennial showdown. The night kicks off at 9pm 31-12-99 and will finish at 5am 02-01-2000. <p> The Friday night boasts a dazzling array of DJs adorning the decks at the hallowed Hanover Grand for a truly distinguished night of hedonistic debauchery. The mighty STETCH & VERN will be the heroes of the night, with their unbridled blend of classy house and an ever dazzling display of deck wizardry. The ever faithful and utterly relentless residents will be going the distance, churning out the finest selection of rare grooves and party tunes for two whole days. Expect to see the unstoppable STEVE AUSTIN hammering the dance floor alongside London’s hottest property, the revered ROCCA and the ardent CRAIG JENSEN. Joining them will be the millennium man MARKIE P, the stupendous SIMON SAYS and Stretch’s faithful sidekick NEIL.<p> Saturday follows with the Herculean Hanover residents holding the fort for those who can handle it. Alternatively you could go home, get that well needed kip and return to Mayfair when the venue officially re-opens on Saturday night at 11pm. The HANGOVER GRAND session will be brought to you courtesy of the notorious nutcases of dance ALEX P and BRANDON BLOCK, who will be whipping up a frenzy for the newly dawned millennium alongside the tireless residents. Make your first day of the next 1000 years one that’s worth remembering - if you can handle it!?</font></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</td>
    <td width="156" bgcolor="#002D42"><p align="center"></td>
  </tr>
